## Non-negotiable verdicts (Afenda contract)

These apply to **every** scoped refactor regardless of module.

### Architecture

```txt
MUST keep ERP/domain business logic in lib/features/<module>/ — never in app/, proxy.ts, or lib/erp/ (primitives only).
MUST keep app/ thin: params, guards, single feature RSC export or equivalent wiring.
MUST import cross-module code only via #features/<module> public doors — no deep cross-module imports.
MUST use #lib/auth for session/org guards — never #lib/tenant.
MUST use Server Actions for internal mutations unless AGENTS.md explicitly allows a Route Handler family.
MUST respect module barrels: index.ts (RSC/server), client.ts (client-safe), server.ts (server-only) where they exist.
```

### UI shelf and design system

```txt
MUST import UI primitives via #components2/ui/* only.
MUST NOT recreate or mkdir repo-root components/ — hard-deleted; forward-only.
MUST use semantic design tokens — no hardcoded hex or one-off geometry outside the design contract.
MUST follow layout ownership: shell owns viewport; route layout owns surface; page owns content flow (frontend-quality-contract §11).
```

### Metadata-driven UI (when REFACTOR_KIND includes metadata-ui)

```txt
MUST treat ADR-0026 as architectural authority for renderer contracts, schema ownership, and feature integration.
MUST use existing governed-surface schemas, renderer registries, and section primitives.
MUST keep feature builders as pure server builders returning validated renderer configuration inputs.
MUST NOT build runtime JSON-to-JSX or low-code ERP surfaces.
MUST NOT put tenant, session, or permission authority in client metadata.
MUST NOT emit design-reserve renderer types without shipped renderer + registry/contract parity.
MUST NOT create a second metadata architecture inside any module.
```

### Next.js runtime

```txt
MUST default to Server Components.
MUST keep client islands narrow — interactivity, browser APIs, form state, optimistic UI only.
MUST pass only serializable props server → client.
MUST await params, searchParams, cookies(), headers() in App Router surfaces.
MUST parallelize independent fetches (Promise.all) — no avoidable waterfalls.
MUST NOT fetch initial ERP data from Client Components.
MUST NOT add segment dynamic/revalidate/runtime exports under app/ (Cache Components doctrine).
```

### Quality and discipline

```txt
MUST apply DRY, KISS, YAGNI — no speculative abstractions.
MUST NOT add new dependencies unless strictly necessary and justified in the report.
MUST NOT leave dead exports, compatibility shims, or redirects to deleted routes (no-dead-code-no-aliases).
MUST NOT use banned directory categories: services, utils, helpers, repositories, controllers (except lib/utils.ts cn() door).
MUST NOT ask the human to run db:generate, db:migrate:local, or DB reset — agent-owned per AGENTS Priority #1.
```

Full boundary table: `AGENTS.md` § Non-negotiable boundaries.

